# Parent reads a value forwarded from an intermediate (`mid`) that has
# itself applied a design adding a new parameter on the leaf. Even though
# the parent never sees `apply` or `squared` directly, the addition lands
# on the deep leaf instance and the value flows up through `mid`'s own
# `Variable::External` reference.
#
# Verifies:
#   - the apply pass propagates additions to the right grandchild
#     instance even when the apply is declared one level down,
#   - parent reads `mid.forwarded` and gets the augmented value; the
#     `External` reference resolves through the same instance subtree
#     that `mid`'s apply augmented.

submodel mid as m

# y = mid.forwarded = squared.l = base * base = 16
Squared via mid: y = forwarded.m
